=Description=

Sara Silva et al. :

"Tarun Bharat Sangh (TBS), operating in India's arid and semi-arid regions
for nearly 50 years, has dedicated itself to restoring water abundance,
reviving river watersheds, and promoting sustainable development.
Responding to villages devastated by water crises,
TBS's work highlights the importance of transcending geographical and
cultural boundaries to regenerate ecosystems and enhance sustainable
livelihoods, offering a replicable model for similar efforts worldwide.
Achievements to date include the revival of 14 rivers, an increase in forest
cover by 30%, turning 70% of barren land into cultivable land, saving five
rivers from encroachment, and training over 25,000 water
conservationists. TBS has also built a network of 10,000 'Jal Yodhas'
(Water Warriors)."

(https://ecolise.eu/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Bioregional-Governance-Training-Guide.pdf?)



